{"id":18298,"date":"2014-02-28T17:04:12","date_gmt":"2014-02-28T13:04:12","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=18298"},"modified":"2022-07-29T10:58:18","modified_gmt":"2022-07-29T06:58:18","slug":"people-change-fate","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/02\/28\/people-change-fate\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Qadr: People may change their fate in the end"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>You must not be impressed with anyone until you see their end. Verily, a servant may perform righteous deeds throughout his life, or for a long time. If he were to die in that state, he would enter Paradise, but then he changes himself and commits evil deeds. Verily, a servant may commit evil deeds for a long time. If he were to die in that state, he would enter Hellfire, but then he changes himself and forms righteous deeds. If Allah intends goodness for a servant, He puts him into action before his death<\/b>.\u201d They said, O Messenger of Allah, how is he put into action?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<b>He is guided to righteous deeds and he holds firmly to it.<\/b>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: <span class=\"il\">Musnad<\/span> Ah\u0323mad 12214<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Sahih<\/i><\/b> (authentic) according to Al-Arna&#8217;ut<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<b> \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0643\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062c\u064e\u0628\u064f